			<div class="ibox-info"><a href="和" title="和">和</a></div>
		</li>
		
	</ul>
	<div class="ibox-image"><a href="./File:Chinese-grammar-wiki-he.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Chinese-grammar-wiki-he.jpg" src="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/0/08/Chinese-grammar-wiki-he.jpg/300px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-he.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/0/08/Chinese-grammar-wiki-he.jpg/450px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-he.jpg 1.5x, https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/0/08/Chinese-grammar-wiki-he.jpg/600px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-he.jpg 2x" /></a></div>
</div> 
<p>You probably learned early on that 和 (hé) is used as an "<a href="And" title="And">and</a>" word to connect <a href="Noun" title="Noun">nouns</a> and noun phrases,  but <i>not</i> sentences or clauses. This rule is fine for a while but eventually you will begin encountering what appears to be non-nouns linked by 和. This article addresses how you may see 和 used in other ways.
</p><p>It's worth mentioning that none of these uses of 和 <i>needs</i> to be <i>used</i>. You could do just fine only using 和 to connect nouns and noun phrases, and native speakers may prefer <i>not</i> to use 和 in some of the examples sentences given below. Still, uses like these <i>do</i> exist.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2>Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="Expressing_&quot;and&quot;_with_&quot;he&quot;_(advanced)#Linking_Verbs_with_.E5.92.8C"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Linking Verbs with 和</span></a>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-2"><a href="Expressing_&quot;and&quot;_with_&quot;he&quot;_(advanced)#Structure"><span class="tocnumber">1.1</span> <span class="toctext">Structure</span></a></li>
